This paper discusses the use of dropout in training deep belief networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of dropout in convex empirical risk minimizers and generalized linear models, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of differential privacy, which is a topic in data privacy and security (cs.DS).
